Public Lease/Loan Sample Contracts: 

CONSUMER FINANCIAL PROTECTION BUREAU (CFPB) – CONTRACT-RELATED DATA:

1. CFPB AUTO LOAN & LEASE CONSUMER GUIDES

OFFICIAL LINK:
https://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/documents/cfpb_auto_loan_guide.pdf

Data Present:
- Structure of auto loan and lease agreements
- Definitions of financial terms:
   a) APR (Annual Percentage Rate)
   b) Monthly payment
   c) Loan/lease term
   d) Down payment
   e) Total cost of financing
- Sample disclosure-style contract languag
- Common fees and charges in auto finance contracts

Use in Project:
- Reference for identifying financial clauses
- Helps train LLM to recognize contract terms
- Improves explanation of clauses to consumers


2. CFPB AUTO LOAN SHOPPING WORKSHEET

Official Link:
https://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/documents/cfpb_auto_loan_worksheet.pdf

Data Present:
- Structured comparison fields
   a) Interest rate
   b) Monthly payment
   c) Loan duration
   d) Total loan cost
- Tabular format for comparing multiple loan offers

Use in Project:
- Helps validate extracted SLA fields
- Used to design contract comparison dashboard
- Supports fairness analysis between offers

3. CFPB CONSUMER LEASING ACT (REGULATION M)

Official Link:
https://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/documents/102012_cfpb_consumer-leasing-act_procedures.pdf

Data Present:
- Legal definitions of lease-specific clauses
- Mandatory lease disclosures:
  a) Lease term
  b) Mileage limits
  c) Excess mileage charges
  d) Early termination penalties
  e)Purchase option / buyout price
- Standardized disclosure language

Use in Project:
- Identification of mandatory lease clauses
- Detection of missing or unclear disclosures
- Compliance and contract fairness evaluation

4. CFPB AUTOMOBILE FINANCE EXAMINATION PROCEDURES

Official Link:
https://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/documents/201908_cfpb_automobile-finance-examination-procedures.pdf

Data Present:
- Auto finance regulatory practices
- Examples of:
  a) Interest calculation methods
  b) Fee structures
  c) Penalty clauses
-Guidelines for fair lending practices

Use in Project:
- Identification of risky or unfair clauses
- Defining red-flag rules in contract analysis
- Supporting negotiation recommendations

5. CFPB “ASK CFPB” – CONTRACT TERMINOLOGY RESOURCE

Official Link:
https://www.consumerfinance.gov/ask-cfpb/

Data Present:
- Plain-language explanations of:
  a) Auto loans
  b) Lease agreements
  c) Fees, penalties, and interest terms
- Consumer-focused Q&A format

Use in Project:
- Simplifying legal language for users
- Enhancing chatbot explanations
- Improving consumer understanding of contracts

NOTE:CFPB does not provide full dealership lease or loan contract PDFs
CFPB resources provide:
  - Authoritative clause definitions
  - Legal disclosure standards
  - Consumer protection guidance
These resources are suitable and valid for academic and research projects


VEHICLES APIS:

1. NHTSA VEHICLE API

Official Link:
https://vpic.nhtsa.dot.gov/api/
- The NHTSA (National Highway Traffic Safety Administration) Vehicle API is an official data source provided by the United States government. 
It offers reliable and verified vehicle-related information, which is essential for validating vehicle details mentioned in car lease and loan contracts.

Information Available:
- VIN (Vehicle Identification Number) decoding
- Vehicle make, model, and year
- Manufacturer and production details
- Body type and vehicle class
- Safety ratings and compliance data
- Recall and defect information
- Consumer complaints and safety-related issues

Usage in the Project:
- This API is used to verify the authenticity of vehicle details extracted from contracts and
to identify potential safety or recall-related risks associated with a vehicle.

2. DATA.GOV VEHICLE DATASETS

Official Link:
https://catalog.data.gov/dataset/?tags=vehicles
- Data.gov is the official open data platform of the U.S. government. It provides access to a wide range of 
vehicle-related datasets published by federal and state agencies.

Information Available:
- Vehicle registration and ownership statistics
- Fuel type and emissions data
- Electric and hybrid vehicle adoption data
- Transportation, mobility, and traffic-related statistics

Usage in the Project:

These datasets are used for analytical and contextual insights, helping the system understand broader
vehicle trends and support data-driven comparisons during contract evaluation.

3. EDMUNDS VEHICLE API (LEGACY)

Official Link:
https://developer.edmunds.com
- The Edmunds Vehicle API (legacy) provides commercially curated vehicle information commonly used in the automotive industry.
Although free access is limited, it remains valuable for academic and reference purposes.

Information Available:
- Detailed vehicle specifications and trims
- Pricing information and MSRP detail
- Ownership, depreciation, and maintenance cost estimates

Usage in the Project:
This API is used as a reference source for pricing and specification comparison, supporting fair market value estimation and negotiation insights.

4. OPENDATASOFT VEHICLE DATASETS

Official Link:
https://public.opendatasoft.com/
- OpenDataSoft provides publicly accessible datasets from various global sources, including vehicle-related reference data.

Information Available:
- Vehicle model and manufacturer details
- Fuel type and basic technical specifications
- Engine capacity and transmission information

Usage in the Project:
-This data is useful for validating vehicle model and specification details mentioned in contracts, 
especially when cross-verifying information obtained from other APIs


